            <h1>Persons with disabilities</h1>
            <div class="temaMobIngressImg" style="display: none;"></div>
            <p class="textIngress">Persons with disabilities shall have opportunities for personal development, participation and self-realisation on a par with other citizens. Everyone shall have equal rights and be able, as far as possible, to decide over his or her own life. </p>
            
            <div class="descriptionTextFull"><p><img alt="Disabled people" src="/upload/AID/temabilder/funksjonshemmede/tema_funksjonshemmede01_150x113.jpg" align="left" />The Government will take steps to enable people with disabilities to exercise their rights and fulfil their obligations as citizens. The Anti-Discrimination and Accessibility Act took effect 1.1.2009. The Anti-Discrimination Ombud is responsible for enforcing the Act.&nbsp;The Government has also started the work on a new Action Plan on Accessibility, among other things to follow up the new Act. </p>
<p>The Government bases its efforts in this field on the principles of social equality and universal design. People who live with functional impairments must be assured living conditions and a quality of life on a par with the rest of the population. The Government believes that the mainstreaming or sector-responsibility is a necessary and basic strategy for achieving the main objectives of the policy relating to persons with disabilities. This strategy means that it is the same public bodies that are to provide and finance services to persons with disabilities as to the rest of the population.<br /></p></div>
